overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to ensure all acceptance criteria from the SOW and
  detailed specification were met. The assistant first performed a detailed
  analysis of the existing codebase, identifying several critical gaps. A
  structured plan was then presented, outlining high, medium, and low priority
  missing features. Following plan approval, the assistant proceeded to
  implement key high-priority items. This included integrating a 1-10 severity
  scale for tiredness interference, complete with safety warnings for high
  scores. Detection and reporting for COMISA (Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea)
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome were added to both the web and PDF reports,
  along with tailored recommendations. Finally, a dedicated section for external
  resources and links to sleep specialists and mental health providers was
  incorporated into the reports, enhancing the application's utility and
  guidance for users.
